main event: A military observation reported a sighting of a spherical object in the Pacific Ocean on February 19, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as spherical, 16 feet in diameter, and bright white in color., The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute., The object disappeared at a 60-degree angle in just 1 second., There was no sound emitted from the object and no visible trail was seen., The sighting was considered as possibly a satellite or satellite debris by the captain.
witness description: Officers from the US Navy, including a Lieutenant junior grade and an ensign, with varying estimates of reliability.
